article.description: Jake LaRavia had 20 points and 10 rebounds as Indiana State won its eighth consecutive home game, topping Bradley 61-53 on Saturday.
article.headline: LaRavia scores 20 to carry Indiana St. past Bradley 61-53
article.linkText: LaRavia scores 20 to carry Indiana St. past Bradley 61-53
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. -- Jake LaRavia had 20 points and 10 rebounds as Indiana State won its eighth consecutive home game, topping Bradley 61-53 on Saturday. LaRavia shot 8 for 10 from the free-throw line. He added four blocks. Christian Williams had 13 points for Indiana State (11-8, 4-4 Missouri Valley Conference). Tyreke Key added 10 points. Jordan Barnes had nine rebounds. Bradley scored 20 points in the second half, a season low for the team. Ari Boya had 14 points and 12 rebounds for the Braves (14-7, 5-3). Danya Kingsby added 12 points and six assists. Ja'Shon Henry had 10 points. Indiana State matches up against Drake at home on Wednesday. Bradley plays Valparaiso at home on Wednesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
